  "title": "Quantity Surveyor Assistant",
  "description": "<p>The Quantity Surveyor Assistant reports to the Quantity Surveyor and assists in all cost and contractual reports on Main contract as well as Sub-contracts connected to the project. </p><p>A summary of the scope of works for this position is, and not limited to, as follows: </p><ul><li><p>Preparation of Monthly Consumption reports for Client. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Preparation of Manpower Report for BCA. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Receiving and sorting out of Delivery orders from the site storeman on site items. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Assisting QS to do cost coding by preparing relevant information. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Collating and compiling cost allocation sheets for approval and reporting. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Ad-hoc duties such as filing and liaison with subcontractors. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p><p>Adherence to safety practices in the workplace. </p><p></p><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 2 years working experience in tendering, estimating and measurement of quantities on buildings projects worth at least $50 million. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Good analytical skills </p></li></ul><p>technical competencies    </p><ul><li><p>Knowledge of materials and works for site usage </p></li></ul></li></ul>",
